This paper discusses sample selection bias correction techniques commonly used in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also analyzes the effect of estimation techniques on the accuracy of the learning algorithm, which relates to the sub-categories of cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CV, followed by cs.ST and cs.DS.
